Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @sweet potato{1} into ½-inch pieces. (TIP: Peel if desired.) Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1}(peeled) into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss sweet potato, bell pepper, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @harissa powder{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. TIP: If you prefer a milder flavor, use less harissa powder.

Roast on top rack until veggies are tender, ~{22-25%minutes}. (You'll add more to the sheet after 10 minutes.)

While veggies roast, zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, @harissa powder{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings), a squeeze of lemon juice, @salt{}, pepper, a pinch of lemon zest to taste, and garlic to taste (you'll use the remaining garlic in step 4). Stir in @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Once veggies have roasted ~{10%minutes}, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully stir veggies, then push to one side of baking sheet. Toss zucchini on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, add zucchini to a second baking sheet; leave veggies roasting and add zucchini to middle rack.)

Return to top rack until all veggies are tender, ~{12-15%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground turkey{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Turkish spice blend{1%tbsp}, remaining garlic, @salt{1/2%tsp} (we used ¾ tsp), and @pepper{pinch}. (For 4 servings, use 1 1/2 tsp salt.)

Form into 6 (12 for 4) 1 1/2-inch meatballs. TIP: Wet hands or coat with oil first to prevent sticking.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{}, preferably #nonstick{}, over medium-high heat. Add meatballs to pan and gently press down with a #spatula{} to make ½-inch-thick patties. (For 4 servings, cook patties in batches if necessary.) Cook until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Sprinkle roasted veggies and roasted zucchini with half the @feta cheese{1/4%cup} and half the remaining lemon zest; stir to combine.

Divide between plates. Top with patties. Drizzle with as much smoky lemon crema as you like. Garnish with remaining @feta cheese{1/4%cup} and lemon zest. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.